Preheat your #oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt and @pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{18-20%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of oil and a knob of @?butter in a #medium saucepan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt and @pepper and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden and softened, ~{8-10%mins}. Halfway through cooking, add the @diced chorizo{90%grams} to the pan. Stir-fry until browned, ~{3-4%mins}.

Add the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%mins} more.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay onto a baking tray, cut-side up. Spread over half the garlic and drizzle over the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the garlic bread. Set aside.

Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{160%grams} and @butter beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Add the remaining garlic and @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) to the onion and fry for ~{1%min} more.

Stir through the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @creme fraiche{75%grams}, @vegetable stock paste{15%grams}, butter beans, sweetcorn and @water{150%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer the sauce until thickened slightly, ~{5-6%mins}.

Bake the garlic ciabatta on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{4-5%mins}.

Meanwhile, stir the roasted sweet potato and @honey{15%grams} into the stew.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Taste the stew and season with @salt and @pepper as needed. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Share the creamy Cajun chorizo stew between your bowls.

Serve with your garlic ciabatta alongside.

Enjoy!